.SH NAME
ath5k_hw_set_sleep_clock \- Setup sleep clock operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ath5k_hw_set_sleep_clock
.BI "(struct ath5k_hw *ah "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ah" 12
The \fIstruct ath5k_hw\fP
.IP "enable" 12
Enable sleep clock operation (false to disable)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If there is an external 32KHz crystal available, use it
as ref. clock instead of 32/40MHz clock and baseband clocks
to save power during sleep or restore normal 32/40MHz
operation.
.SH "NOTE"
When operating on 32KHz certain PHY registers (27 - 31,
123 - 127) require delay on access.
